      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHY SHOULD SHE (2) is looking to continue her winning ways off a good 21.90 success in a Maiden at this track. Has the ability and looks hard to top. ARCHER TWELVE (1) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner three back (22.24) at this track over 375m. Key player on best and worth another try. DON'T TELL MILLY (5) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at her last six runs. Last time finished 3rd in a Grade 5 on April 26 over 375m at this track behind Wrinkled Henry beaten 7 lengths (22.61). Will give a great sight again. PURE GOUT (4) is always hard to beat when she races at this trip.",
